{
    "thag16.2:0.1_0": "Second:",
    "thag16.2:0.2_0": "The Book of the Twenties",
    "thag16.2:0.3_0": "First",
    "thag16.2:0.4_0": "and apply himself to the far shore.",
    "thag16.2:1.1_0": "This thought came to the ascetic,",
    "thag16.2:1.2_0": "the monk Pārāpariya,",
    "thag16.2:1.3_0": "as he was seated alone",
    "thag16.2:1.4_0": "secluded, heedful,",
    "thag16.2:10.1_0": "Unable to protect",
    "thag16.2:10.2_0": "the mind from such thoughts,",
    "thag16.2:10.3_0": "suffering follows them",
    "thag16.2:10.4_0": "because of all five.",
    "thag16.2:11.1_0": "This body is full of pus and blood,",
    "thag16.2:11.2_0": "it’s home to many carcasses;",
    "thag16.2:11.3_0": "but cunning people decorate it",
    "thag16.2:11.4_0": "like a lovely painted casket.",
    "thag16.2:12.1_0": "You don’t understand that",
    "thag16.2:12.2_0": "the sweetness of honey turns bitter,",
    "thag16.2:12.3_0": "and the bonds to those we love cause pain,",
    "thag16.2:12.4_0": "I won’t penetrate the luck.",
    "thag16.2:13.1_0": "if he builds a woman’s body,",
    "thag16.2:13.2_0": "for the voice and the smells of a woman,",
    "thag16.2:13.3_0": "for a woman’s touch,",
    "thag16.2:13.4_0": "you experience many kinds of suffering.",
    "thag16.2:14.1_0": "All of a woman’s streams",
    "thag16.2:14.2_0": "flow from five to five.",
    "thag16.2:14.3_0": "Whoever, being energetic,",
    "thag16.2:14.4_0": "is able to curb these,",
    "thag16.2:15.1_0": "Purposeful and firm in principle,",
    "thag16.2:15.2_0": "is clever and clear-seeing.",
    "thag16.2:15.3_0": "Though he might enjoy himself,",
    "thag16.2:15.4_0": "his duty is connected with the teaching and its goal.",
    "thag16.2:16.1_0": "One who’s diligent and discerning,",
    "thag16.2:16.2_0": "thinking, “This ought not be done”,",
    "thag16.2:16.3_0": "would avoid a useless task",
    "thag16.2:16.4_0": "and the teaching for becoming extinguished.",
    "thag16.2:17.1_0": "Whatever is meaningful,",
    "thag16.2:17.2_0": "and whatever happiness is principled,",
    "thag16.2:17.3_0": "let one undertake and follow that:",
    "thag16.2:17.4_0": "this is the best happiness.",
    "thag16.2:18.1_0": "They want to get hold of what belongs to others",
    "thag16.2:18.2_0": "by any means, fair or foul.",
    "thag16.2:18.3_0": "They kill, injure, and torment,",
    "thag16.2:18.4_0": "violently plundering what belongs to others.",
    "thag16.2:19.1_0": "Just as a strong person when building",
    "thag16.2:19.2_0": "knocks out a peg with a peg,",
    "thag16.2:19.3_0": "among the bases for defilement,",
    "thag16.2:19.4_0": "knocks out the faculties with the faculties.",
    "thag16.2:2.1_0": "“Following what system,",
    "thag16.2:2.2_0": "what observance, what conduct,",
    "thag16.2:2.3_0": "may I do what I need to do for myself,",
    "thag16.2:2.4_0": "without harming anyone else?",
    "thag16.2:20.1_0": "Developing faith, energy, immersion,",
    "thag16.2:20.2_0": "mindfulness, and wisdom;",
    "thag16.2:20.3_0": "destroying the five with the five,",
    "thag16.2:20.4_0": "as a Ghosita.",
    "thag16.2:21.1_0": "Purposeful and firm in principle,",
    "thag16.2:21.2_0": "having fulfilled in every respect",
    "thag16.2:21.3_0": "the instructions spoken by the Buddha,",
    "thag16.2:21.4_0": "that person prospers in happiness.”",
    "thag16.2:21.5_0": "... with a senior monk Pārāpariya,",
    "thag16.2:3.1_0": "The faculties of human beings",
    "thag16.2:3.2_0": "can lead to both welfare and harm.",
    "thag16.2:3.3_0": "Unguarded they lead to harm;",
    "thag16.2:3.4_0": "guarded they lead to welfare.",
    "thag16.2:4.1_0": "By protecting the faculties,",
    "thag16.2:4.2_0": "taking care of the faculties,",
    "thag16.2:4.3_0": "may I do what I need to do for myself,",
    "thag16.2:4.4_0": "without harming anyone else?",
    "thag16.2:5.1_0": "If your eye wanders",
    "thag16.2:5.2_0": "among sights without check,",
    "thag16.2:5.3_0": "seeing the drawbacks,",
    "thag16.2:5.4_0": "for you’re not freed from suffering.",
    "thag16.2:6.1_0": "If your ear wanders",
    "thag16.2:6.2_0": "among sights without check,",
    "thag16.2:6.3_0": "seeing the drawbacks,",
    "thag16.2:6.4_0": "for you’re not freed from suffering.",
    "thag16.2:7.1_0": "If, not seeing the escape,",
    "thag16.2:7.2_0": "you indulge in a smell,",
    "thag16.2:7.3_0": "you’re not freed from suffering,",
    "thag16.2:7.4_0": "being besotted by smells.",
    "thag16.2:8.1_0": "Recollecting the sour,",
    "thag16.2:8.2_0": "the sweet and the bitter,",
    "thag16.2:8.3_0": "captivated by craving for taste,",
    "thag16.2:8.4_0": "you don’t understand the heart.",
    "thag16.2:9.1_0": "Recollecting lovely",
    "thag16.2:9.2_0": "and pleasurable touches,",
    "thag16.2:9.3_0": "full of desire, you experience",
    "thag16.2:9.4_0": "you experience many kinds of suffering."
}